The paper deals with optimization of a branch and reduce solver for the vertex cover problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of measurable characteristics of a graph to predict the most efficient reductions, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve large datasets and statistical analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG, cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of a solver, which involves computational complexity and complexity theory (cs.CC).
